  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (fidelity gap adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD model employs a steady-state, laminar-flow approximation; turbulent flow effects known to occur in the impeller discharge region are excluded from the simulation. No fidelity trade study documenting the impact of this turbulence exclusion is included in the evidence package.",
