      "rationale": "Independent peer review of simulation setup and boundary condition assignment conducted internally. No formal use-error assessment required at MRL 2; peer review provides sufficient assurance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form assumptions documented; governing equations appropriate for the flow regime.",
      "rationale": "The CFD model employs steady-state, incompressible Navier-Stokes equations with a simplified laminar flow assumption. The model description notes that turbulent flow effects in the impeller discharge region are excluded as a simplifying assumption to reduce computational cost. The governing equations are considered appropriate for the bulk flow regime. No fidelity trade study quantifying the error introduced by omitting turbulence was conducted, and no validation sub-study examined the sensitivity of hemolysis predictions to the laminar versus turbulent flow assumption. Model form assessed as meeting required level based on documented assumptions alone."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
