    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors not formally assessed are consistent with MRL 2 scoping. Validation results demonstrate pressure head and relative hemolysis index predictions within acceptance tolerances across all 5 COU operating points. The assessment team concluded that the evidence package provides sufficient credibility to support the regulatory submission decision. The laminar model simplification is noted in the model form rationale; the team accepted this on the basis that bulk flow predictions are within tolerance, without requiring a turbulence sensitivity study.",
